"Since he's a carpenter, he might have some occupational exposure to bacteria or viruses, which could lead to infections.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054755,0.10068,0.10619,0.10086,0.09439,0.090277,0.090357,0.085219,0.080765,0.079344,0.065729,0.051426],"unified_progress":[0.080708,0.11084,0.10072,0.096724,0.09102,0.090987,0.085347,0.088062,0.07759,0.071796,0.060346,0.045865]},{"section":6,"text":"The fact that he has a wound infection on his left thumb suggests that the infection might be spreading or the immune system is responding, possibly causing the lymph node to enlarge.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.071781,0.092905,0.097539,0.099181,0.090939,0.088609,0.088477,0.084126,0.079928,0.07685,0.068815,0.060851],"unified_progress":[0.080221,0.093756,0.093714,0.095259,0.091187,0.09192,0.086803,0.088328,0.080412,0.074806,0.066509,0.057083]},{"section":7,"text":"Looking at the biopsy results: follicular enlargement and hyperemia.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054255,0.086839,0.090632,0.098348,0.093609,0.0915,0.091398,0.084997,0.08017,0.079453,0.076284,0.072514],"unified_progress":[0.047723,0.078678,0.088262,0.098462,0.097445,0.094164,0.092738,0.088348,0.087189,0.082788,0.07481,0.069392]},{"section":8,"text":"Follicular enlargement in lymph nodes is often seen in infections, like bacterial or viral infections.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041082,0.059773,0.077445,0.088913,0.098713,0.10253,0.10444,0.10266,0.097446,0.087923,0.073463,0.065618],"unified_progress":[0.039648,0.06503,0.085042,0.094606,0.099328,0.10976,0.10241,0.098291,0.092269,0.085738,0.07118,0.056698]},{"section":9,"text":"The hyperemia (redness) could indicate inflammation.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.05281,0.069403,0.082731,0.091656,0.097781,0.099986,0.10012,0.095056,0.089676,0.080786,0.073543,0.066455],"unified_progress":[0.054677,0.076072,0.086431,0.092467,0.096983,0.098718,0.095969,0.093971,0.089363,0.081913,0.072619,0.060817]},{"section":10,"text":"The sinuses being filled with neutrophils points towards a bacterial infection because neutrophils are a type of white blood cell that responds to infections, especially bacterial ones.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042787,0.057536,0.079722,0.091549,0.10383,0.10707,0.1078,0.10038,0.093836,0.081771,0.070661,0.063047],"unified_progress":[0.043661,0.067721,0.087328,0.095144,0.10076,0.10507,0.10241,0.095886,0.090471,0.083408,0.071171,0.05697]},{"section":11,"text":"I'm thinking about the possible pathogens.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053518,0.09727,0.088999,0.091238,0.086193,0.0837,0.086129,0.083071,0.083312,0.093413,0.084208,0.068949],"unified_progress":[0.034575,0.071744,0.084728,0.099982,0.098227,0.095133,0.095739,0.093972,0.090281,0.092308,0.07874,0.064572]},{"section":12,"text":"Since he's a carpenter, maybe he's exposed to Staphylococcus aureus, which is common in environments with skin breaks or wounds.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046909,0.085848,0.093879,0.089159,0.091947,0.092073,0.093335,0.092523,0.090989,0.087918,0.075648,0.059771],"unified_progress":[0.070561,0.099549,0.093456,0.090685,0.090884,0.092518,0.088741,0.090631,0.082617,0.077379,0.067597,0.055382]},{"section":13,"text":"Staph infections can cause abscesses and lymph node enlargement.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036786,0.054221,0.07107,0.081633,0.096942,0.10415,0.10705,0.10974,0.10591,0.09267,0.075695,0.064127],"unified_progress":[0.039147,0.06296,0.09473,0.096636,0.10105,0.11018,0.10368,0.097926,0.091418,0.083587,0.066723,0.051966]},{"section":14,"text":"Another possibility is a viral infection like the Epstein-Barr virus (EBV), which can cause lymphadenopathy, but EBV is more common in certain age groups and presentations.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025069,0.047935,0.067756,0.079945,0.094393,0.1034,0.10874,0.11386,0.11203,0.10152,0.083087,0.06227],"unified_progress":[0.032406,0.06136,0.083155,0.095526,0.10108,0.10709,0.10613,0.10379,0.097205,0.093062,0.070412,0.048787]},{"section":15,"text":"However, the presence of neutrophils leans more towards a bacterial cause.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037348,0.051377,0.068037,0.077816,0.085233,0.092045,0.097032,0.10202,0.10435,0.1044,0.099098,0.081249],"unified_progress":[0.037825,0.058856,0.073518,0.082925,0.091504,0.094146,0.09676,0.10122,0.099634,0.10336,0.088798,0.071457]},{"section":16,"text":"The fact that the sinuses are filled with neutrophils is a key clue.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043452,0.05899,0.070302,0.08016,0.086068,0.090542,0.094443,0.093957,0.094132,0.093557,0.095848,0.098549],"unified_progress":[0.040351,0.062549,0.07492,0.084867,0.089033,0.09144,0.093502,0.093322,0.094696,0.091573,0.091644,0.092104]},{"section":17,"text":"In bacterial infections, the body sends neutrophils to the site of infection to fight it off, which can lead to abscess formation.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040734,0.049382,0.066656,0.078602,0.093291,0.10156,0.10568,0.10854,0.10636,0.094818,0.080861,0.073525],"unified_progress":[0.03869,0.05782,0.078201,0.088874,0.096229,0.10909,0.10389,0.10174,0.096972,0.091489,0.076575,0.060427]},{"section":18,"text":"This is different from viral infections, where T cells are more prominent in the response.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03391,0.047324,0.066301,0.078167,0.091869,0.10056,0.10549,0.11046,0.10951,0.10005,0.086835,0.06953],"unified_progress":[0.034341,0.05692,0.076828,0.089041,0.096927,0.10361,0.10408,0.10392,0.099774,0.09834,0.078263,0.057955]},{"section":19,"text":"So putting it all together, the combination of a wound infection, axillary lymph node enlargement, and biopsy findings of follicular hyperplasia with neutrophils in the sinuses points towards a bacterial infection, likely Staphylococcal.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020515,0.031604,0.040515,0.047614,0.053081,0.060138,0.067233,0.080238,0.094128,0.11402,0.15473,0.23619],"unified_progress":[0.020312,0.032864,0.041157,0.05128,0.056407,0.071109,0.072572,0.086737,0.09667,0.10545,0.15227,0.21318]},{"section":20,"text":"The carpenter's occupation makes Staphylococcus aureus a likely culprit.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029256,0.045852,0.054503,0.05858,0.063658,0.069987,0.077891,0.087615,0.099134,0.11329,0.13202,0.16822],"unified_progress":[0.039258,0.054204,0.055115,0.058885,0.064258,0.07312,0.076566,0.089444,0.097001,0.10499,0.12622,0.16094]},{"section":21,"text":"Therefore, the diagnosis is likely Staphylococcal lymphadenitis.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019687,0.037167,0.046321,0.052919,0.057887,0.063731,0.070896,0.081241,0.09357,0.11486,0.14716,0.21457],"unified_progress":[0.020098,0.036816,0.045935,0.054666,0.059683,0.068732,0.074626,0.085631,0.096702,0.1088,0.14523,0.20308]},{"section":22,"text":"...your internal reasoning for the diagnosis...","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043716,0.079184,0.071659,0.073881,0.072327,0.073555,0.079444,0.082307,0.090566,0.11203,0.11725,0.10408],"unified_progress":[0.028202,0.055548,0.066139,0.079113,0.081901,0.08652,0.09237,0.09704,0.10184,0.11106,0.10697,0.093291]},{"section":23,"text":"The patient is a 20-year-old carpenter with a wound infection on his left thumb, presenting with an enlarged and tender axillary lymph node.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053507,0.10455,0.089827,0.080966,0.070646,0.069449,0.071406,0.072982,0.076861,0.085592,0.10309,0.12113],"unified_progress":[0.059488